false,"model_progress":[0.038761,0.074725,0.085432,0.08974,0.090283,0.089492,0.091139,0.090014,0.088742,0.090612,0.084233,0.086827],"unified_progress":[0.042272,0.062414,0.072567,0.081923,0.087184,0.091006,0.092522,0.094739,0.095439,0.096937,0.094269,0.088729]},{"section":14,"text":"Other causes of C1 inhibitor issues?","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037064,0.074694,0.088976,0.094464,0.094962,0.092326,0.09308,0.09105,0.087884,0.089628,0.080298,0.075574],"unified_progress":[0.038987,0.065511,0.078902,0.08897,0.092896,0.094601,0.097249,0.095863,0.094273,0.094638,0.08535,0.07276]},{"section":15,"text":"Maybe acquired, but the patient is young, so hereditary is more likely.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032988,0.068091,0.080599,0.087638,0.092646,0.098237,0.097198,0.097259,0.094534,0.093684,0.084769,0.072356],"unified_progress":[0.060784,0.090233,0.086141,0.085762,0.087647,0.088478,0.088581,0.092742,0.088256,0.087842,0.078708,0.064826]},{"section":16,"text":"I think the most likely diagnosis here is Hereditary Angioedema Type I, since Type I and II both have low C1 inhibitor, but Type III has normal levels but functional defect.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030654,0.062962,0.075818,0.086245,0.093163,0.096221,0.098879,0.095366,0.090807,0.092304,0.085026,0.092556],"unified_progress":[0.036211,0.058388,0.078808,0.083766,0.089471,0.097636,0.095228,0.093945,0.091878,0.090986,0.090774,0.09291]},{"section":17,"text":"Since the lab says deficiency (so low quantity), it's Type I.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033677,0.069446,0.08303,0.088971,0.091488,0.091967,0.095031,0.093182,0.091803,0.088652,0.085882,0.086871],"unified_progress":[0.049644,0.066433,0.077319,0.084442,0.089705,0.090743,0.091964,0.090966,0.089933,0.087626,0.090033,0.091192]},{"section":18,"text":"But the question just asks for the disease name, not the type.","dimensio